bwOCSCommonCommStatsTable.name: bwOCSCommonCommStatsTable
bwOCSCommonCommStatsTable.description: This table contains counters for BCCT for the OCS process.

bwOCSCommonCommStatsEntry.name: bwOCSCommonCommStatsEntry
bwOCSCommonCommStatsEntry.description: Definition of the entries for bwOCSCommonCommStatsTable.

bwOCSCommonCommStatsIndex.name: bwOCSCommonCommStatsIndex
bwOCSCommonCommStatsIndex.description: This integer represents an index in table bwCommonCommPSStatsTable. The index represents a connection for a specific Host-Interfacece-Protocol combination.

bwOCSCommonCommHost.name: bwOCSCommonCommHost
bwOCSCommonCommHost.description: The address of a host connected to the BroadWorks Common Communication Protocol.

bwOCSCommonCommInterface.name: bwOCSCommonCommInterface
bwOCSCommonCommInterface.description: The IP address of a local interface that a protocol is bound to.

bwOCSCommonCommProtocol.name: bwOCSCommonCommProtocol
bwOCSCommonCommProtocol.description: The name of a BroadWorks Common Communication Protocol client protocol, e.g. OCI or SyncApi.

bwOCSCommonCommAcceptedOutboundConnectio.name: bwOCSCommonCommAcceptedOutboundConnections
bwOCSCommonCommAcceptedOutboundConnectio.description: This counter is incremented whenever a client in this process connects to the framework to a remote host, using the interface and protocol.

bwOCSCommonCommAcceptedInboundConnection.name: bwOCSCommonCommAcceptedInboundConnections
bwOCSCommonCommAcceptedInboundConnection.description: This counter is incremented whenever a client in this process connects to the framework from a remote host, using the interface and protocol.

bwOCSCommonCommRejectedOutboundConnectio.name: bwOCSCommonCommRejectedOutboundConnections
bwOCSCommonCommRejectedOutboundConnectio.description: This counter is incremented whenever a client connection request going from this process to a remote host and going through this interface has been rejected for a particular protocol.

bwOCSCommonCommRejectedInboundConnection.name: bwOCSCommonCommRejectedInboundConnections
bwOCSCommonCommRejectedInboundConnection.description: This counter is incremented whenever a client connection request coming to this host and going through this interface has been rejected by the framework for a particular protocol.

bwOCSCommonCommOutputMessagesProcessed.name: bwOCSCommonCommOutputMessagesProcessed
bwOCSCommonCommOutputMessagesProcessed.description: This counter is incremented whenever a message has been sent and processed for this host, interface and protocol.

bwOCSCommonCommInputMessagesProcessed.name: bwOCSCommonCommInputMessagesProcessed
bwOCSCommonCommInputMessagesProcessed.description: This counter is incremented whenever a message has been received and processed for this host, interface and protocol.

bwOCSCommonCommOutputCommunicationErrors.name: bwOCSCommonCommOutputCommunicationErrors
bwOCSCommonCommOutputCommunicationErrors.description: This counter is incremented whenever a message could not be read because the TCP stack returned an error.

bwOCSCommonCommInputCommunicationErrors.name: bwOCSCommonCommInputCommunicationErrors
bwOCSCommonCommInputCommunicationErrors.description: This counter is incremented whenever a message has been sent and processed for this host, interface and protocol.

bwOCSWASProcessingErrors.name: bwOCSWASProcessingErrors
bwOCSWASProcessingErrors.description: This counter is incremented every time the OCS cannot connect to the WAS.

bwOCSTcpServersNbBytesSent.name: bwOCSTcpServersNbBytesSent

bwOCSTcpServersNbBytesReceived.name: bwOCSTcpServersNbBytesReceived
bwOCSTcpServersNbBytesReceived.description: This counter represents the number of bytes received by the TCP server.

bwOCSTcpServersIncomingQueueSize.name: bwOCSTcpServersIncomingQueueSize
bwOCSTcpServersIncomingQueueSize.description: This counter represents the number of bytes in the incoming queue.

bwOCSTcpServersNbBytesSentSecure.name: bwOCSTcpServersNbBytesSentSecure

bwOCSTcpServersNbBytesReceivedSecure.name: bwOCSTcpServersNbBytesReceivedSecure
bwOCSTcpServersNbBytesReceivedSecure.description: This counter represents the number of bytes received by the TCP server over secure connections.

bwOCSReserved.description: This is a reserved counter not used to report any particular value.
